    "ideation": "The floppy disk animation captures the mechanical lifecycle of vintage magnetic storage. The face acts as the disk drive: starting in a static, ready-to-receive state with a 'gray' metallic color. The mouth represents the read/write head movement, shifting from a flat line to a dense, high-frequency rattle during data access. The eyes act as the drive's activity LED, blinking from a dim standby green to a bright, rapid-flicker amber. The arc follows the disk being inserted, the system struggling to read a sector with a tense 'gritted' mouth, the successful data transfer surge, and finally the satisfying mechanical 'click' of the eject button.",
